# The ONLY value you must set is JINA_API_KEY below. Everything else is commented out
# with working defaults; uncomment only to override.
#
# Apple Silicon (Mac, no Docker): see docs/MAC.md and run via scripts/mac-run.sh. MTP
# speculative decoding works on llama.cpp >= 9430 (Homebrew) — use the MTP GGUF from
# unsloth/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-MTP-GGUF and set SPEC_ARGS='--spec-type draft-mtp --spec-draft-n-max 2'
# (~1.23x decode speedup). For older builds, use the non-MTP GGUF and leave SPEC_ARGS empty.
# Set EMBED_DEVICE=cpu and lower CTX_SIZE (e.g. 65536) to fit unified memory.
#
# Jina API key — powers the jina CLI (search/read/rerank/...) and downloads
# jina-embeddings-v5-nano. Get one free at https://jina.ai/api-dashboard/
# Replace jina_xxxx with your real key (setup.sh refuses to start on the placeholder).
JINA_API_KEY=jina_xxxx

# Pin the llama.cpp image to an immutable digest (the default tag is a moving target).
#   docker buildx imagetools inspect ghcr.io/ggml-org/llama.cpp:server-cuda  # copy the sha256
# LLAMA_IMAGE=ghcr.io/ggml-org/llama.cpp@sha256:<digest>

# Context window for the LLM (= llama-server --ctx-size, and the dashboard/compaction
# denominator). Default targets Qwen3.6's full 131072. This hybrid GDN+MoE model has only
# 10/40 KV-bearing layers, so q4_0 KV at 131072 is only ~0.65GB on the L4; the Q4_K_XL weights
# (~22GB) are what fill the card. Measured ~22.2GB at full ctx. Lower (e.g. 98304/65536) only if
# nvidia-smi shows you are tight. Keep CTX_SIZE, CONTEXT_WINDOW, and the dashboard in sync.
# CTX_SIZE=131072

# --- Switching the model ------------------------------------------------------
# ONE knob: MODEL=<hf_repo>/<file.gguf>. setup.sh derives the download repo + filename from it
# and persists MODEL_FILE for docker-compose (--model), so download and serve stay in sync. To
# switch the LLM, set MODEL and re-run scripts/setup.sh. Default = Qwen3.6 MTP Q4_K_XL.
# MODEL=unsloth/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-MTP-GGUF/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-UD-Q4_K_XL.gguf
#
# Advanced overrides (rarely needed); leave unset to use the defaults derived from MODEL:
# MODEL_ID=qwen3.6                                    # agent-side label only; need not match the GGUF
# CHAT_TEMPLATE_FILE=/templates/chat_template.jinja   # Jinja template in the llama-server container
# SPEC_ARGS=--spec-type draft-mtp --spec-draft-n-max 2  # MTP/draft flags (reference MTP-L4 tune)
#
# Switching to a NON-Qwen GGUF is not just a filename swap: point CHAT_TEMPLATE_FILE at that
# model's own Jinja template (a wrong template silently corrupts tool-calling/reasoning), set
# SPEC_ARGS= (empty) unless the GGUF ships an MTP draft head, and lower CTX_SIZE for a dense
# model (it uses far more KV per token than this hybrid and may OOM the L4). Re-check VRAM with
# nvidia-smi. To use the GGUF's own embedded chat template, drop --chat-template-file from the
# docker-compose command (an empty CHAT_TEMPLATE_FILE still passes an empty arg).

# --- Outcome-based stopping ---------------------------------------------------
# The job runs until the dataroom is comprehensive (the FLOOR), not for a fixed time.
# DONE is rejected by the orchestrator until the floor is met.
# MIN_FILES=100                # substantive sourced files (topics/ + reports/) required
# MIN_FILE_BYTES=500           # a file smaller than this does not count as substantive
# SATURATION_WINDOW=3          # consecutive low-progress turns that count as diminishing returns
# MIN_NEW_FILES_PER_TURN=2     # below this per turn (over the window) = saturated
# CONSOLIDATE_EVERY=4          # every Nth cycle is a forced read+merge consolidation pass (0=off)

# --- Hard safety ceilings (backstops; the loop normally stops on the floor/saturation) ------
# MAX_SECONDS=21600            # 6h wall-clock backstop
# MAX_TURNS=300                # turn backstop
# MAX_JINA_CALLS=2000          # paid Jina CLI (jina search/read/...) call budget
# TURN_TIMEOUT=1200            # per-turn timeout
